libght
------------------------------------------
A file format and library for storing and rapidly accessing point cloud data,
in particular LIDAR data.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.4-1
  libght-devel-0.1.0-1bl1
  libght0-0.1.0-1bl1
  libxml2-2.9.9-2
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-9.2.0-3
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/pramsey/libght

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/pramsey/libght/archive/v0.1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libght-0.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libght-0.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libght-0.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libght-0.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libght0-0.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libght-devel-0.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libght)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libght.README
  /usr/share/doc/libght/COPYRIGHT
  /usr/share/doc/libght/README.rst

(libght0)
  /usr/bin/libght-0.dll

(libght-devel)
  /usr/include/ght.h
  /usr/include/ght_core.h
  /usr/lib/libght.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libght.pc

------------------

